Module chav1961.purelib
Package chav1961.purelib.enumerations

Enum ContinueMode

java.lang.Object
java.lang.Enum<ContinueMode>
chav1961.purelib.enumerations.ContinueMode
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<ContinueMode>, java.lang.constant.Constable
public enum ContinueMode
extends java.lang.Enum<ContinueMode>

This enumeration describes continue mode for any walkers (firstly tree walker). This enumeration is used usually as return code of the walking methods. In conjunction with NodeEnterMode it supports walking on the linked structures for different walking methods

Since:
0.0.2
Author:
Alexander Chernomyrdin aka chav1961
See Also:
NodeEnterMode

  • Enum Constant Summary

    Enum Constants 
    Enum Constant Description
    CONTINUE
    Continue walking
    PARENT_ONLY
    Walk from current node to the root only
    SIBLINGS_ONLY
    Move to siblings only, don't walk to parent or children nodes
    SKIP_CHILDREN
    Skip children and continue on the current level
    SKIP_PARENT
    Don't walk up to the root
    SKIP_SIBLINGS
    Skip siblings and return to the previous level
    STOP
    Stop walking immediately
